==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Low
<hw>Low</hw> <pr>(l⟦omac⟧)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Lowed</conjf> <pr>(l⟦omac⟧d)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Lowing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[OE. <ets>lowen</ets>,
AS. <ets>hl⟦omac⟧wan</ets>; akin to D. <ets>loeijen</ets>, OHG.
<ets>hl⟦omac⟧jan</ets>, <ets>hluojan</ets>.]</ety> <def>To make the
calling sound of cows and other bovine animals; to moo.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>lowing</qex> herd wind slowly o'er the lea.</q>
<rj><qau>Gray.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Low</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Low
<hw>Low</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The calling sound ordinarily made by
cows and other bovine animals.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Talking voices and the <qex>law</qex> of herds.</q>
<rj><qau>Wordsworth.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Low</ent>⟦br⟧

